                "description": "Byte Kitchen is on a mission to bring America’s best restaurants to every neighborhood in the country through our novel operating model. We partner with stand-out restaurants and recreate their food for delivery in new markets, simultaneously expanding brand equity and consumer choice.\r\n\r\nByte Kitchen is backed by leading investors including Y-Combinator, Crosslink Capital, WndrCo, Soma Capital and strategic angels. We are a small and rapidly expanding team, and are seeking entrepreneurial individuals to join us.\r\n\r\nWe are obsessed with what makes a great user experience - and we’re developing the tools that make it possible top to bottom in the antiquated, multi - Trillion dollar food service industry.\r\n\r\n### **Your role:**\r\n\r\nWe are seeking a full stack developer to build products that streamline both our backend operations and frontend user experience. You will be tasked with leading the development of a vertically integrated tech stack for our multi-concept kitchens, building some nodes from scratch while integrating existing off-the-shelf solutions where appropriate. \r\n\r\nAs an early member of the team you will have significant autonomy, and be involved in both the day-to-day and strategic decisions of Byte Kitchen. You will steer the direction of our technology products, and join an engineering culture that champions empathy for the end user. If you are passionate about building technology to power the future of the restaurant industry, this is the right role for you.\r\n\r\n### **Responsibilities:**\r\n\r\nBuild and guide our growing team and evolving product as an early technology team member\r\n\r\nDevelop an in-depth understanding of our business model, space, and end user\r\n\r\nAssist in developing our technology roadmap for both the near and long term\r\n\r\nWork closely with the founding team on product direction decisions and strategy\r\n\r\nApproach tired problems with impassioned energy and creative solutions\r\n\r\nWork with the founders to attract and employ likewise impassioned engineers set on bringing BK's vision to life.\r\n\r\n\r\n### **Ideal experience:**\r\n\r\n4+ years experience as a full stack engineer/ solutions architect\r\n\r\nProficiency in front end languages (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) and Javascript Frameworks (React)\r\n\r\nProficiency in server-side languages (NodeJS ideal)\r\n\r\nExperience with Cloud (AWS, Firestore ideal)\r\n\r\nComfort with Database technology (MySQL, Postgres)\r\n\r\nExperience building products from scratch\r\n\r\nExcellent problem solving and communication skills\r\n\r\n**Bonus:**\r\n\r\nStartup experience / experience in food tech or logistics companies\r\n\r\n### **You are:**\r\n\r\n**Scrappy:** you know when to prioritize speed over scalability and are comfortable making those decisions\r\n\r\n**Comfortable with ambiguity:** some things you work on may never become full products. But one might change the course of this industry\r\n\r\n**Delighted to take ownership:** you alone decide the ceiling of the scope of your responsibilities\r\n\r\n### **We are:**\r\n\r\n**Customer obsessed:** we serve two customers – our restaurant partners and the end consumers. Every decision we take is focused on improving experience for both\r\n\r\n**Hungry:** to build a solution which is a true partnership for restaurants; to create the kitchen of the future; to bring the best food to our customers every day\r\n\r\n**Collaborative:** we have no time for office politics, everyone takes out the trash, all opinions are not only welcome but highly encouraged  \r\n \r\n### **Compensation:**\r\nYou will receive competitive compensation with meaningful equity for a seed stage startup, amazing food and a collaborative, respectful and inclusive work environment. We don’t pretend to have all the answers. But we do have an obsessive focus to figure them out and we want every single person’s input on the team to do so.\r\n\r\nAt Byte Kitchen, we firmly believe there is only one way to build a sustainable business model in the food delivery industry – be a true partner to restaurants. If you want to be part of a dynamic team that is transforming the way restaurants expand, please reach out to us.\r\n ",
