                "description": "#### About Bluedot\r\nBluedot is an early-stage startup backed by Y Combinator. We raised a pre-seed round (Y Combinator, Axel Springer and Porsche, First Round Capital's Dorm Room Fund, TechNexus, Ford + many cool angel investors). At Bluedot we love what we do and believe our diverse team of ridiculously ambitious, humble, hungry, driven people is what makes our company great.\r\n\r\n#### Our Values\r\n\r\n⋅⋅* Action: We take initiative. We are doers, not bystanders.\r\n\r\n⋅⋅* Boldness: We don’t tinker, we transform.\r\n\r\n⋅⋅* Customer-Centered: Our customers are at the core of our business. Delivering for them is our North Star.\r\n⋅⋅* Diligence & Dedication: We do what we say we’re going to do, when we say we’re going to do it.\r\n⋅⋅* Entrepreneurial: Act like an entrepreneur not an employee, generate results for the company and customers everyday.\r\n\r\n#### Requirements:\r\n⋅⋅* A degree related to online/digital marketing, communication or a similar field\r\n⋅⋅* Excellent English written and communication skills\r\n⋅⋅* Fast learner, eager to learn\r\n⋅⋅* Advanced analytical skills\r\n⋅⋅* Committed & proactive\r\n⋅⋅* Strong attention to detail & organizational skills\r\n⋅⋅* Team player, enthusiastic individual with highly developed interpersonal skills\r\n⋅⋅* Initiative & proactivity, ability to identify problems/obstacles, make recommendations and follow through with solutions\r\n\r\n#### Responsibilities:\r\n⋅⋅* Being part of the create online advertising creatives for different channels\r\n⋅⋅* Stay current with design trends, social media memes, and other cultural phenomena to contribute fresh and innovative ideas for new concepts\r\n⋅⋅* Support in the creation and sending of emails, sms and push notifications\r\n⋅⋅* Take care of the creation of marketing articles of any kind for all channels (blog posts, social media, newsletters, professional articles, case studies.)\r\n⋅⋅* Plan the content calendar and take care of the design and publication of inspiring content across social media\r\n⋅⋅* Analyze the effectiveness of the content as well as the communication channels and develop measures to optimize them\r\n⋅⋅* Analyze the performance of our social media content, build reports and generate key learnings from it\r\n⋅⋅*Do competitive and industry research\r\n\r\n####Perfect match if you are:\r\n⋅⋅*You are proactive, creative & have a positive learning attitude. Being able to do research and propose additional marketing activities across social media platforms (Instagram, Twitter and Linkedin)\r\n⋅⋅*You are organized and detail oriented. Being able to maintain a detailed calendar for the social media planning\r\n⋅⋅*You are creative and have an eye for design\r\n⋅⋅*You have a Marketing/Communications/Design/Social Media background or education\r\n⋅⋅*You are a multitasker who enjoys checking things off your list\r\n⋅⋅*You understand that working for a startup means you occasionally need to be flexible in your job role\r\n\r\nIf you are passionate about marketing and have a desire to learn, grow and contribute to a dynamic team, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.\r\n",
