                "interview_process": "Our marketing internship process is designed to be comprehensive and thoughtful, allowing us to identify the best candidates for the role and ensure a good cultural fit with our team. The process consists of four key stages:\r\n\r\n⋅⋅*Meeting with Marketing Lead:\r\nIn this initial stage, you'll meet with our Marketing Lead to discuss the role and its responsibilities. You'll learn more about our company, our marketing goals, and what we're looking for in a marketing intern. The Marketing Lead will also share details about the work you'll be doing and the skills you'll need to succeed in the role.\r\n\r\n⋅⋅*Case study:\r\nTo assess your marketing skills and creativity, we'll ask you to complete a case study. You'll be given a real-world marketing challenge that our team has faced, and we'll ask you to develop a plan or strategy to address it. This will allow us to evaluate your problem-solving skills, strategic thinking, and marketing expertise.\r\n\r\n⋅⋅*Culture fit meeting with co-founders:\r\nWe believe that cultural fit is essential for a successful internship, so we'll schedule a meeting with our co-founders to discuss your alignment with our company values and goals. This meeting will be an opportunity for you to learn more about our company culture, vision, and mission, and for us to assess how well you fit into our team.\r\n\r\n⋅⋅*Offer:\r\nIf you successfully complete all three stages, we'll extend an offer for you to join our team as a marketing intern. The offer will include details about compensation, work hours, and any other relevant information you need to know. We'll also work with you to ensure a smooth onboarding process, so you can start your internship with confidence.",
