              "description":"CareRev is a technology platform empowering healthcare professionals to take control of their careers. CareRev provides a direct line between healthcare facilities and local clinical talent, cutting out the middleman and enabling professionals to work where and when they want. Together, we’re building the local, resilient, flexible healthcare workforce of the future. CareRev serves over 32 major metropolitan areas nationwide at over 70 hospitals and health systems, and over 540 outpatient centers and skilled nursing facilities. More than 22,000 clinical professionals (and growing!) are included in CareRev’s network. For more information, visit www.carerev.com or follow us on LinkedIn.\r\n\r\nAs a Senior Engineering Manager at CareRev you will be responsible for managing Engineering Managers, the people and projects on 2-3 product delivery teams (about 8-12 total people). You will work closely with individuals to help them achieve their absolute best at CareRev. You will solicit feedback, assess it, and together with the individuals you manage help put together a program of high achievement and stellar career growth. Additionally, you will be deep in the weeds with your teams day to day, helping to break down work and establish and monitor metrics for your team's functional areas and team performance. Working closely with your engineering management peers, you'll gather feedback from your teams and help continuously evolve the engineering organization.You will engage with other departments to ensure understanding and alignment across the company.\r\n\r\n**What You'll Do:**\r\n\r\n- Develop a robust team to reach their highest potential by implementing roadmaps, individual/team, and a vision for the function.\r\n- Build and create a function that strives to reach their highest potential by providing support, tools, and insights to the team.\r\n- Drive the delivery of features and big fixes by working with the engineers, product managers, and designers on your teams to weigh scope, time, cost, resources, quality, and risk.\r\n- Have expert knowledge of your projects - what needs to happen next, what's done, who's doing what, where the hidden challenges lie.\r\n- Apply your deep understanding of cutting-edge tools, methodologies, and skillsets to create a diverse team with achievable goals.\r\n- Forecast the needs of your team; from creating value propositions for new roles to leveling the role and team accordingly.\r\n\r\n**What We're Looking For:**\r\n\r\n- 3+ years of experience building, managing, and mentoring 2 or more high-performing engineering teams in a high-growth start-up.\r\n- 5+ years of hands-on coding experience with at least 2+ years on building and shipping Ruby on Rails apps or equivalent in production.\r\n- Ability to navigate ambiguity and provide actionable goals for your team that relates to your function and the overall vision for the company.\r\n- Excellent people manager with a record of building, managing, and retaining talent.\r\n- Deep understanding and utilization of various engineering and project management tools and methodologies.\r\n- Outstanding written and verbal communication skills and a strong ability to articulate complex ideas to both a technical and non-technical audience.\r\n- A strong bias towards breaking down projects into smaller deliverables and shipping code often, but not recklessly\r\n- BS or MS in Computer Science or a related field, or equivalent work experience.\r\n\r\n**It would be even better if you have…**\r\n\r\n- B2C experience is good, but B2B is even better\r\n- 2+ years in a Healthcare startup. Industry knowledge is not required, but is especially helpful when it comes to healthcare.\r\n- Functional programming experience (or at least enthusiasm).\r\n- Strong understanding of CI and build pipelines\r\n- Solid working knowledge of containerization, k8s, and general cloud engineering principles (ideally via AWS)\r\n- Experience establishing and maintaining engineering metrics\r\n\r\nThe anticipated salary range for this position is $123,000.00 - $254,000.00. Equity, bonus or commission and benefits may also be provided as part of the total compensation package, depending on the position offered. If given an offer, the exact salary amount offered will ultimately depend on multiple factors, which may include the successful candidate's skills, experience, education and other qualifications as well as the candidate's location of residence.\r\n\r\n**Reasons to Consider Us:**\r\n\r\n- 100% remote company\r\n- Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision benefits\r\n- Short term disability 100% covered by CareRev\r\n- Life insurance covered by CareRev\r\n- Fertility health and family-planning benefits\r\n- Paid parental leave\r\n- Generous paid holidays & unlimited PTO\r\n- 401K and company match\r\n- Competitive Stock Options\r\n- Employee Assistance Program\r\n- Employee discount network\r\n- Pet Insurance\r\n- Learning reimbursement program\r\n- Home office set-up equipment stipend\r\n\r\n**Physical Requirements:**\r\n\r\n- Prolonged periods of sitting and/or standing at a desk\r\n- Prolonged periods of working on a computer\r\n- Repeating motions that may include the wrists, hands and/or fingers\r\n- Ability to lift up to 15 pounds of work equipment\r\n- Ability to set up home office to include desk and chair\r\n\r\n**CareRev** is committed to the full inclusion of all qualified individuals. In keeping with our commitment, we will take the steps to assure that people with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodations. Accordingly, if reasonable accommodation is required to fully participate in the job application or interview process, to perform the essential functions of the position, and/or to receive all other benefits and privileges of employment, please discuss with your Recruiter.\r\n\r\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and will not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment in an unlawful manner. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all individuals. CareRev treats all employees and job applicants based on merit, qualifications, and competence without regard to any qualified individuals' sex, race, color, religion, national origin, ancestry, gender (including pregnancy, breastfeeding, or related medical condition), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, physical or mental disability, medical condition, genetic characteristic or information, marital status, military, and veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by state or federal law. CareRev also considers qualified applicants with criminal histories consistent with applicable local, state, and federal law.",
