              "title":"Sales, Partnerships and BDR Leader",
              "skills":[

              ],
              "description":"Samos Business Development Representative (BDR) & Partnerships Management\r\n\r\nThe Company\r\n\r\nSamos is a venture-backed Insurtech with a vision to protect customers by filling gaps in their traditional coverages while also providing on-demand peace of mind when customers and their families need it most. \r\n\r\nOur inaugural product is foundational built upon our proprietary data model and translated into our insurance user interface that we envision providing protection for millions of worldwide customers every year. A World's first, Samos' Surgery Insure product protects patients and their families providing accidental death insurance coverage during their surgery and supportive resources.\r\n\r\nOur team and products have been recognized as innovative by many of the preeminent global insurance companies and reinsurance companies on the planet. As a proud Y Combinator company, we have had positive validation and backing from the investor community to accelerate growth.\r\n\r\nThe Role\r\n\r\nSamos is seeking a driven Business Development Representative (BDR) and Partnerships Manager to lead the development and execution of the company’s sales through three distinct channels across multiple business verticals in Canada. You will bring knowledge and contacts specific to these channels and verticals.\r\n\r\nThe role will work closely with the Founding team along with the product and marketing team in order to identify, cultivate, structure and close complex deals within sophisticated distribution channels.\r\n\r\nThis is an opportunity to join an organization that will nobly help customers and where we wholeheartedly believe we will disrupt and change the World's largest industry for the better - that's a bold statement, but we've already done it and we aren't stopping.  The BDR and Partnerships Manager will be a pivotal role in building and leading the organization in its early stages in Canada. \r\n\r\nWhat does a work week will look like for you?\r\n\r\nPlan\r\nDevise a sales strategy and revenue targets in a manner that's been proven from your prior successful experience\r\nBuild a best practice \"machine\" for sales and customer relationship management based on data and quantitative measures.\r\nLeveraging your knowledge and experience to build a process for partnership identification, onboarding and deployments\r\n\r\nExecute\r\nIdentify, nurture, structure and close sales opportunities\r\nIdentify, nurture, negotiate and secure win-win partnerships that ultimately lead to fulfilling revenue targets\r\nNurture and leverage your network connections to build and cultivate a circle of influential decision makers in order to target sales opportunities\r\nActively nurture and develop partnerships to maximize value for the business.\r\n\r\nPartner\r\nTake a leadership role with cross-functional teams to ensure pitches are delivered effectively to prospective partners with clarity on the Samos solution and opportunity.\r\nOnboard new partners ensuring timely delivery of solutions that meet or exceed client expectations.\r\nServe as resident expert on the market solution with in depth knowledge  and communicate your business requirements to internal stakeholders in a clear and concise manner.\r\nGrow the Samos brand within your network and through representation at industry and broader networking events.\r\n\r\nMeasure\r\nRegularly evaluate production results by the Samos sales function and distribution partners to ensure achievement of goals\r\nMonitor the execution of specific initiatives and achievement of distribution goals and make adjustments to initiatives as necessary\r\nMonitor publicly-available information to maintain in-depth knowledge of partner/distributor performance, strategies, and direction\r\nSupport company objectives with the development of fact-based, data-driven regional and national distribution strategies\r\nUtilize appropriate insurance platforms and other data-driven distribution tools to optimize distribution strategy and support targeted business initiatives\r\n\r\nRequired Skills/Experience\r\n\r\nKey Competencies:\r\n\r\nProven strategic and critical thinking capabilities\r\nSound leadership and influencing capabilities\r\nUnderstanding of Canadian financial services marketplace\r\nExcellent interpersonal skills, including ability to effectively interact with team members at all levels within Samos and its distribution partners\r\nExcellent written and oral communication skills and executive presence\r\nExceptional organizational and project management skills\r\nAble to connect dots/see patterns across projects and the organization\r\nExcellent problem-solving and organizational skills; ability to manage multiple priorities work\r\nDemonstrate a high level of personal initiative, setting and achieving challenging goals\r\n\r\nPreferred Technical Skills:\r\nDemonstrated proficiency in the Microsoft products (Excel, PowerPoint, Word and Outlook) and/or Google Suite of products (Sheets, Slides, Docs, Gmail, Drive, Meet)\r\n\r\nExperience:\r\nExperience developing and implementing growth strategies across multiple lines of business\r\n\r\nEducation:\r\nBachelor degree preferred\r\n",
