              "title":"Electric Aircraft Powertrain and Performance Engineer",
              "skills":[

              ],
              "description":"We're looking for an experienced Electric Powertrain and Performance Engineer to join us in developing novel electric fixed-wing drones that achieve real-world ranges and payloads that will read like a typo compared to the competition. \r\n\r\n\r\n**What you'll do :**\r\n\r\nYou’ll join a lean team of engineers in the design and development of (at first) novel drones that fly over water in ground effect, and (later) those that operate with extreme efficiency in all capacities and situations\r\n.\r\nYou’ll take the initiative for technical development of powertrain/propulsion systems and components for both small-scale prototypes and full-scale versions, and be a positive hands-on contributor to the building and testing of hardware that's continually exposed to harsh environmental conditions.\r\n\r\nYou will obtain and analyze detailed performance data from models, benchtop tests, and field testing (flight data), and verify and validate that data.\r\n\r\nYou'll develop and use physics-based computer tools to analyze aircraft performance in various mission scenarios - with a particular emphasis on energy efficiency - to help underpin the overall design and development of our products.\r\n\r\nYou’ll have responsibility for setting (and meeting!) specific and ambitious electric power system requirements for a full craft, and you'll educate your collaborators on the why and the how.\r\n\r\nYou’ll be a comfortable communicator to different types of internal and external stakeholders - strong emphasis on ability to convey complex content or ideas with effective visuals. \r\n\r\n\r\n**Who you are :**\r\n\r\nYou love airplanes. \r\n\r\n*Experience*\r\n\r\nMinimum 3 years in a private industry/applied R&D setting working on design and development of electrified mobility systems, preferably from the conceptual through to real hardware deployment.\r\n\r\nSpecific electric aviation powertrain experience is valued, but equivalent expertise (e.g. automotive) that has good crossover works too.\r\n\r\nYou have direct personal experience in – and passion for - prototyping and very rapid incremental testing and development of systems.\r\n\r\nYou're comfortable with Matlab and Python, or are excited to learn quickly based on your other prior experience with other codes.\r\n\r\nYou have led or mentored other engineers in some professional capacity, and have experience managing your own work or a small team to successful completion of milestones.\r\n\r\nDesirable: working self-sufficiently with suppliers and vendors.\r\n\r\n\r\n*Your approach to work*\r\n\r\nYou have a commitment to quality when it comes to generating and analyzing data. Attention to detail while also still moving fast and often adapting to change.\r\n\r\nVibrant curiosity; you take a keen interest in the product and the tools and processes you use, to continually improve the work of the whole company and deepen your own knowledge and capability.\r\n\r\nExtremely high levels of self-motivation – this is a small team that requires everyone to take the initiative, even if it’s in areas outside their comfort zone\r\n\r\nYou have the ability to collaborate and communicate effectively with empathy, and with a particular emphasis on visual communication. \r\n\r\n\r\n*Education*\r\n\r\nBachelors or higher degree in electrical engineering, or aerospace/aeronautical/mechanical/strongly related field.\r\n\r\n\r\n*You must also :*\r\n\r\nHave the existing right to work in the US (we are not supporting new visas at this time unless you are a Canadian or Australian citizen)\r\n\r\nBe able to start work with us inside 8 weeks from offer accepted.\r\n\r\nBe available for full time work on-site in Carson, Los Angeles (remote work flexibility will be available once you are up and running but this is majority in-person – we have flying machines to build!)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Who We Are**\r\n\r\nSeaflight is a company on a mission to accelerate an electric and equitable future for flight. And we’re doing it with friendly robots! We design, build, test and manufacture uncrewed (drone) electric flying machines to deliver cargo with world-beating aerodynamic efficiency.\r\n\r\nWe celebrate differences and are committed to a diverse workplace that fosters inclusion for employees from different backgrounds and experiences. You see sentences like that that a lot, so here’s the most obvious real example - sure, we’re dealing with small number statistics right now, but our current workforce is 50% female and features citizens of 4 different countries.  \r\n\r\n\r\n**Benefits**\r\n\r\nFlexible time off (just need manager approval)\r\n\r\nEmployee equity\r\n\r\nHealth insurance: medical, vision, dental, short-term disability, and life\r\n\r\nRelocation assistance\r\n\r\nFlexible hours (deliverable-based goals)\r\n\r\nPersonal recognition for your work through technical publishing, social media features, industry events",
